- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a fully distributed and asynchronous implementation of the HyperANF algorithm for calculating graph statistics. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper deals with graph-based data and its application in IoT contexts. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of graph statistics in distributed coordination and situation recognition, which can be seen as control problems. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a possible category as the paper discusses network vulnerabilities detection. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of the HyperANF algorithm for calculating graph statistics.
